  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Water &amp; Top School Spots for Tea Plantation Kids</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Children of tea plantation workers dream of escaping a future in the fields by excelling on the Scholarship Exam in their final year of primary school. All who do well can earn a place in a well-funded national school and a scholarship. A teacher is ready to expand a successful tutoring program. We&apos;ll build a room that doubles as a library and replace an unhealthy latrine with a flush toilet and hand washing station. Then we&apos;ll train parents as community organizers who can solve future issues.</narrative>
  </description>
